41","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1392":"1392","1428":"1428","1416":"1416","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Crewe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Crew  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Crew","meanings":["English: habitational name from Crewe in Cheshire or Crew in Cumberland, both named with Old Welsh <i>criu</i> ‘weir’. This denoted a wickerwork fence that was stretched across a river to catch fish."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":16,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When David Crewe was born in 1366, in Cheshire, England, his father, Thomas Crewe, was 28 and his mother, Agnes Airemine, was 25. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan Sound. He died in 1416, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1366–1416":"1366–1416","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1392–Female":"1392–Surnud","1338–1403":"1338–1403","1341–1408":"1341–1408","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","Abt 1392":"umbes 1392","1368":"1368","1366":"1366","1341":"1341","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1392":"1392","1428":"1428","1416":"1416","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1366–1416":"1366–1416","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1392–Female":"1392–Kuollut","1338–1403":"1338–1403","1341–1408":"1341–1408","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","Abt 1392":"noin 1392","1368":"1368","1366":"1366","1341":"1341","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1392":"1392","1428":"1428","1416":"1416","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1366–1416":"1366–1416","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1392–Female":"1392–Décédée","1338–1403":"1338–1403","1341–1408":"1341–1408","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","Abt 1392":"environ 1392","1368":"1368","1366":"1366","1341":"1341","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1392":"1392","1428":"1428","1416":"1416","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque David Crewe est né en 1366, à Cheshire, Angleterre, son père, Thomas Crewe, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Agnes Airemine, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Joan Sound. Il est décédé en 1416, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 50 ans."},"de":{"1366–1416":"1366–1416","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1392–Female":"1392–Verstorben","1338–1403":"1338–1403","1341–1408":"1341–1408","1338":"1338","1403":"1403","Abt 1392":"um 1392","1368":"1368","1366":"136